article.description: — Obadiah Noel scored 24 points as UMass Lowell defeated Hartford 71-62 on Saturday.
article.headline: Noel leads UMass-Lowell over Hartford 71-62
article.story: LOWELL, Mass. -- — Obadiah Noel scored 24 points as UMass Lowell defeated Hartford 71-62 on Saturday. Connor Withers added 20 points for the River Hawks. Withers also had nine rebounds. Salif Boudie had 19 points for UMass Lowell (4-7, 3-4 America East Conference). Bryce Daley added six assists. UMass Lowell scored 36 points in the first half, a season high for the team. Miroslav Stafl had 16 points for the Hawks (7-5, 4-3). Austin Williams added 14 points and six rebounds. Hunter Marks had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
